    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1903-01-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1903-01-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="403"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d403">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Tower</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Embassy of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-01-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 9, 1903</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Tower acknowledges the receipt of the Department’s telegram, and reports
                    that he has communicated to the German minister for foreign affairs President
                    Castro’s answer, as well as Mr. Bowen’s request that the blockade be raised, and
                    the Department’s announcement that Mr. Bowen will come to Washington
                    immediately.</p>
                <p>Baron Richthofen accepted Mr. Tower’s communication, but remarked incidentally
                    that this answer still gives no specific statement as to the payment or security
                    of the claims described in the preliminary conditions.)</p>
            </div>
